body: Wall running- the perfect strategy for many DTM maps such as candy land and Venomous. This is a strategy were you hold down the sprint button, look down, and place block to create a quick bridge. How to do it? It's simple. If you're doing it on the left side of a wall, hold down w, d, and the sprint key. Aim a bit in front of you but underneath you and keep spamming right click. If it's on the right side, do the same thing but use a instead of d. If you are too parallel to the wall, your sprint won't work and you will fall. If you're too perpendicular, the blocks won't place. If you aim too far in front, you might accidentally trip yourself into the void. If you aim too far down, you will over jump. Wall running is a very useful start to get to the other side of a map easily. Use it effectively, and you can break monuments like a ninja. Creds to Sevothesavage (now SevoisTaken) for using this strategy, inspiring me to do so. The is my first large post, so criticism is welcome. Any questions? Ask down below. Any criticism? go right ahead, but for now, ShombieSquid out-
